This paper focuses on the task of dense-captioning events in videos, which involves understanding events in long untrimmed videos. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper proposes different captioning models and evaluates their contributions, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of visual features (cs.MM) in their proposed models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
